Ahead of the 2022 Africa Day, Spotify has rolled out plans to celebrate the milestone with week-long activities. According to sources, The Nation reliably gathered that the audio streaming platform is itching to celebrate African sounds during the 2022 Africa Day celebrations. It was further gathered that Spotify is rolling out drums in celebrating the sounds of Africa on the platform.   BBNaija: Viewers say reality show provided emotional and…     Mercy Aigbe, hubby arrive London for movie premiere     Iyabo Ojo curses blogger alleging daughter dates Kizz Daniel   A special activity, which is yet to be unveiled, has been planned for Wednesday, May 25 in Johannesburg to showcase the voices that make Africa proud. As of April 2022, Spotify released Nigeria’s most popular tracks, albums, and artists with Rema, BNXN aka Buju, Burna Boy, Black Sherif, and YBNL signee, Asake leading the pack. For popular songs listened to by Nigerians, Black Sherif’s Kwaku the Traveller, Pheels and Buju’s Finesse, Asake and Olamide’s Omo Ope, Fireboy DML’s Playboy and Rema’s Calm Down garnered more streams. Spotify has continued to celebrate female African music stars creating a buzz on the international scene with the Equal Africa programme. From Ayra Starr to Asa, Amaarae, DBN Gogo, and Nomfundo Moh, the females have been celebrated by Spotify Equal Africa.